Common.SpaceDescription.Common.Text: Architecturally appealing and idyllically situated on a landscaped campus, this two-story office building consists of 287,580 square feet. The Property is located on a vast 45-acre corporate campus that is approximately 10 miles southeast of downtown Tulsa along U.S. Highway 64. North of the Property, Interstates 44 and 244 connects the property with Tulsa’s major population centers and allows for ease of access from the entire metropolitan area. Benefiting from a low cost of living and a diverse economy, Tulsa ranks among America’s Most Livable Cities” (Forbes). Built in 1989 and recently modernized with over $5 million in capital improvements, the Property’s quality construction, convenient location, and significant capital investment reinforces this Property as a long-term home for any major employer. The Property includes a full service cafeteria, power generator for the entire building, outdoor spaces, and office space for both executive and administrative staff. Total employee capacity could be 1,250. Can be demised for multi-tenant use.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: Situated just over 10 miles southeast from downtown Tulsa, the Property enjoys a highly convenient and visible location along a major east-west thoroughfare connecting it to multiple population centers. The Property‘s suburban location is enhanced by the numerous major highways and interstates that are within a few miles of the site. Interstates 244, 44, U.S. Highway 169 and U.S. Highway 64 (which the Property fronts), creating a truly accessible regional headquarters.
